To ensure machines created by a MachineSet have a unique tag, you need to add tags in the providerSpec of the MachineSet template. The exact field depends on the cloud provider (AWS, Azure, GCP, vSphere, etc.).
I'll show the AWS example since tagging is very common there.


Since you're on Microsoft Azure, MachineSets use AzureMachineProviderSpec, 
and tags are defined in the tags map inside the provider spec. These tags will be applied to the VMs created by the MachineSet.


- name: Create Azure MachineSet
  hosts: localhost
  gather_facts: no
  collections:
    - kubernetes.core

  vars:
    namespace: openshift-machine-api
    cluster_id: mycluster-abcde
    machineset_name: worker-extra
    replicas: 2
    azure_region: eastus
    vm_size: Standard_D4s_v3
    unique_tag: "ansible-{{ lookup('pipe','date +%s') }}"

  tasks:
    - name: Create MachineSet
      kubernetes.core.k8s:
        state: present
        kubeconfig: ~/.kube/config
        definition:
          apiVersion: machine.openshift.io/v1beta1
          kind: MachineSet
          metadata:
            name: "{{ cluster_id }}-{{ machineset_name }}"
            namespace: "{{ namespace }}"
            labels:
              machine.openshift.io/cluster-api-cluster: "{{ cluster_id }}"
          spec:
            replicas: "{{ replicas }}"
            selector:
              matchLabels:
                machine.openshift.io/cluster-api-machineset: "{{ cluster_id }}-{{ machineset_name }}"
            template:
              metadata:
                labels:
                  machine.openshift.io/cluster-api-cluster: "{{ cluster_id }}"
                  machine.openshift.io/cluster-api-machine-role: worker
                  machine.openshift.io/cluster-api-machine-type: worker
                  machine.openshift.io/cluster-api-machineset: "{{ cluster_id }}-{{ machineset_name }}"
              spec:
                providerSpec:
                  value:
                    apiVersion: azureproviderconfig.openshift.io/v1beta1
                    kind: AzureMachineProviderSpec
                    location: "{{ azure_region }}"
                    vmSize: "{{ vm_size }}"
                    managedIdentity: "{{ cluster_id }}-identity"
                    resourceGroup: "{{ cluster_id }}-rg"
                    vnet: "{{ cluster_id }}-vnet"
                    subnet: "{{ cluster_id }}-worker-subnet"

                    tags:
                      environment: dev
                      machineset: "{{ machineset_name }}"
                      deployment_id: "{{ unique_tag }}"
					  
					  
					  
